review_text: This would‚Äôve been a 5 star if there was a restroom.
There's a portapotty but it's always locked :( I've ended up having to cut our park time early because there is no where to take the kids to potty..

One of my favorite parks, but also lacks public restrooms. The dog park is disgusting and nothing but mud no matter what time of year. Could use work into it. Park hosts many events all year round. Safe area. Large. Decent jungle gym. Most of jungle gym is fit for kids who can climb.
a great place
A great place to bring your kids and dogs... it's clean and well kept.

Great little park, the park of Manayunk! With a pretzel in the front and the sidewalk shaped as such it's a great time. Parks on tap and farmers markets here during the summer and every Saturday respectively. Dog Park nearby. Children's playground next to it as well
Cute family friendly park not far from the amazing dining options
Love to sit watch the doggies play
City park. Nice old infrastructure. Well kept. Big, old trees. Playground.

Will maintain and very friendly patrons make this a go-to park especially on a Saturday morning in the summer with the farmers market or really any relaxing day where you can head down to manayunk to enjoy some local food and friendship.
Great little farmers market here on saturdays from 10am-2pm
Awesome experience for my wife, kid, our dogs and myself. Loved everything about the park.
It's awesome
Farmers market there
A neighborhood staple! Clean, family friendly, good vibes. Must check it out during the Farmer‚Äôs market on summer Saturdays!
They planted clover in the grassy areas.
It's part of my childhood @

Adorable, well utilized pocket park with an awesome pretzel statue! Great little playground with lots of tangled webs of wires for free play. Picturesque view of the churches on both sides and hillside homes. Crowded in a good way.
Nice park with some planted beds, some benches for people watching and lunch. Small playground and dog park on site. Good quiet place to enjoy.
Perfect playground for my 18-month old granddaughter. Great equipment for her and older kids, safe soft playing surface, grass too. And we met lots of other kids. We'll be back
Got to experience the farmers market held on Saturdays.  Though the items were priced high it was nice to walk through the park and see all the vendors.
Nice & clean area.
Really great park, got something to kids/adults/dogs in one place!
I like this park it‚Äôs very low-key a great place to bring your family and sometimes they have little events there. They have a cute little dog park there as well.

Really nice cute park, VERY dog-friendly. Kid-friendly also. There's a farmers' market on Saturdays, where you can get wine, candles, produce, and more. Parking is a challenge, but if you live in the area, it's nice to visit on a weekend. The music at the farmers' market is very Johnny-Cash-heavy, but I don't mind. The volunteers are great kind people.
Nice park. Great place for families. Clean and inviting.

Clean.
Free concerts.
Close to eateries.
Relax and people watch.

I love the new ü•® pretzel park! I grew up going to this park and my kids finally had the opportunity to go. The equipment is a lot safer and cleaner and my kids had a ball with all the Parkor type equipment.
Wonderful park for all types of dogs to play in, water for dogs that like water, an open area for the dogs who like to run around and a small wooded trail for the dogs who like to explore.
It's always a beautiful day in Pretzel Park.
A hidden gem with a dog run, kids' playground and Saturday farmer's market.
Clean and well kept

The new pretzel park is so nice and different from most parks, could use a rock wall and maybe better structurally designed climbing gym. Although the new climber is cool it only allows a child to climb minimal. Could use more recreational activities.
Wonderful playground, always clean and everything works beautifully. My kids love it here and there's a nice lawn and dog park as well as some shaded benches. A lovely park.

Such a cute, pet-friendly town to walk around and explore. The Manayunk towpath is great for a nice and quiet stroller walk. This spot has a great variety of cute murals and parks, along with a view of the Manayunk Bridge from the path!
Beautiful
Friendly small park. Usually good street parking. Folks usually bring water.
It's a nice local dog park, but the walls are low and it gets way too muddy.
Awesome little park
Great locations and usually a good amount of pups. Will get muddy often and it‚Äôs all dirt/mulch
This is the perfect neighborhood dog park.  In a  small setting., with good dog peeps.  Our dog loved it.  We will b back.
Nice park to enjoy time with kids, walking the dog and enjoying the outdoors.
Nice park. Kid and pet friendly

Fun
Nastalgic! This was my childhood park. Now I get to share that memory with my baby boy.
Small and very cute park in a nice area close to both manayunk and Roxborough. It's not very big but it's mostly clean and even sometimes will have little farmer/flea markets there
Nice small dog park. Only one section for dogs of all sizes....
Great as usual!
Cute park at the heart of Manayunk. They have a small and nice farmers market in here every Saturday.
A Street park with a dog park attached. Nice
Decent space
A local gem üíé
Nice
Cute little park with a nice market on the weekends
Love coming here it‚Äôs super convenient and the upgraded and safe playground is a huge plus!
Great park
Nice park, hard to find parking.
It's a park!
Great playground. Awesome farmer‚Äôs market on Saturdays
Excellent park...not over populated...
Nice little local playground, some unique equipment we haven't seen in others. Not very big though but does well with the space it's in.
It's a tiny park with a small area for dogs. I wouldn't go out of my way to visit but would go back if I was in the area. There's a nice playground for kids but not much else.

Beautiful park, with serene grassy field sandwiched between a dog park and an amazing rope-course playground. The perfect distance from Main Street Manayunk. Love the stone staircases leading down to Manayunk. The two churches nearby all Chile beautifully on the hour, especially one of them with very on-pitch and extended, beautiful music. Enough trees for shade too, especially when sitting on the benches.
I love this place it's an oasis in the city. Benches , trees playground, baseball field. Memorial

Shady oasis in hilly Manyunk. We discovered this park on a scavenger hunt to "eat" the pretzel sculpture. There's a shady dog park, 2 new playground areas and benches for hanging out. On Saturdays in season, there's a farmer's market. Finding nearby street parking is a challenge, and most entrances to the park are not handicap accessible, but require going up flights of steps. We found a ramp on one corner of the park.
Great place to take your dogs
Parks ok. Surrounding steps, etc,, covered in dog poop. Impossible to sit on steps. Let alone.eat something. Pick up after your.dog please!

Pretzel park playground looks awesome after the renovation, it will be great for the kids on warmer weather. Pretty clean.
By the way, there's a little free library there in the playground, which also serves as a sort of food pantry for the community.
Such a nice park with so many options for play for children both big and small! Absolutely coming back!

The new playground equipment is excellent, great for children of a wide variety of ages.  We enjoy coming here after school and on the weekends and have regular playground friends that we've only seen here.
Bueno
Cute park with a dog park inside.

Great park as fenced dog area one side and a new kids playground on other plus it holds a lot of activity's one moth it may have a flea market next moth a DJ and then a rally and everyone that attended are friendly good place to visit
Nice little park in manayunk. Real close to main street.
Nice long enclosure for ball throwing. I've only been twice but the people and dogs were friendly both times. Does have a big mud pit in the middle.
Great dog park when there aren't self proclaimed "dog psychologists" around.
Great play ground equipment for kids. Doggie enclosed area. Shady and really nice

Great public space! Aside from the pretzel statue, there's enough space to throw a frisbee, read a book on the lawn, take your kids to the playground, or take your more furry kids to the dog park. There's plenty of bench space, places for wheelchair access, and a community book swap (forget what they're called, book drop off of sorts). It's all close by to Main Street, has a weekly farmer's market, and has hosted musicians and plays in the past. Good amount of shade for the summer days as well!
Our favorite place...me and the 3 kids..they love the spinning thing plus space to run, lots of benches, a free book exchange, great climbing structure

Childhood playground!! They always keep up with it and you can follow the committee on IG whenever they have gatherings or free functions there..
Also a dog park tho, while they keep the kids area separate the park is dog friendly so keep in mind.

This is very near my son's home and our grandson loves it. They redid the playground last year and everything is new and there is a soft cushioned ground around the equipment.

On Saturdays, late spring through fall, there is a farmers market in the morning.
Nice park!!!!!

The redesigned playground for children is beautiful and appropriate for all ages. Bonus that the climbing structure is fun for older kids. The park hosts some really nice events for kids and adults that we've enjoyed. Nice little farmer's market on some weekends. The dog park gets muddy in wet weather so be aware of that. Gated and good for a little run around with other dogs. The open space between the playground and dog park is great for a picnic and has a perfect view of the train if you have a little one who would enjoy that.
My grandson loves this park!
Awesome central location. Very fun and unique playground and lots of shade to sit and relax by the benches.
Cool
Nice and clean park and it was cool underneath the trees.
Nice relax place
Old style square with church and park
Great little park in the middle of manayunk
Great park with a gated space for dogs to run around and a playground for the kids.
Nice green spot. Nice pretzel statue. There was a very quick shot of this park in the movie Unbreakable
Adorable little park!
Great little park
Good fenced doggie area

Great place for families with kids and dogs. There's a pretty good playground for the kids and an enclosed dog park for the dogs. Everyone is usually with their dogs and ensuring they get along. Have taken our dogs here many times. Would be cool if it could be leveled out with a top layer that allows the dogs to play but not in dirt. Park otherwise is great and has large trees for shade and picnic areas.

Went to this park because they were hosting a witches market. Fabulous time it was raining rather heavy, however alot of people were out RAIN OR SHINE. The vendors at this event are amazing, great way of making connections. Really enjoyed the atmosphere and the market that day. Pretzel park was big enough to hmmmm ost the 10 to 12 vendors that beautiful sunday afternoon.

A cute LITTLE dog park set on a hill.  It is part of a larger city park.  Parking is tricky, however there's urban beauty all around: beautiful old churches, classic Philadelphia row houses and of course, a place for your dog to play.
This park has come a long way! The Saturday farmers market is worth checking out!
Another good dog park. "New" play ground for kids. Clean and safe. Plenty of summer events.
Good place for a Farmer Market
Park is very small but great for kids and has dog parks for your animals
So beautiful in Fall and Spring! We love the Farmers‚Äô Market!
The Witch Market was rained out...and still lovely. Nice turn out for a drab day.

Pretzel park is a great little park with benches, dog park ,and playground. I was there when they had vendors showcasing their products.My friend showcased her new Tea leaf business. It's Viva Tea leaf all natural with everything grown locally .

It was a wonderful experience for me and my new dog I have a 9 month old American pit terrier and he went out there and play with about six dogs and they had a good time the only thing was that particular day it was a little rainy and muddy so we had to all get money and clean are dogs other than that I'm very happy with the site and I will be coming back and bringing my animal
Such a gem in the middle of Manayunk. There's a dog park, a newly renovated playground, a little free library, and lots of oaks, grassy space, and benches. I love this little park!
Sweet little park, great for smaller kids, has farmers market on Saturday.
Cool park
Nice and clean

As a child, my mom used to take me, as a parent took my children, now I take my dog to the dog park

We discovered this park after dropping our daughter off at Merge Dance Studio! Our son is 2 and it is a great park to challenge him and work on his balance skills. We bring our scooters as well too! Plenty of parking nearby if needed.

Great place to bring the kids. I just think they should have vending machines or at least sell pretzels.... Hence the name. Other than that i give it an A+ for cleanliness of the park, & updated equipment.
Great place to throw crab apples and rocks at each other.
Look out for the Great Weiner Run. It‚Äôs the cutest fundraiser I‚Äôve ever been to!
Clean and we'll kept
Nice jungle gym for kids. Farmers market 10-2pm on Sundays!
Very well kept park in Manayunk.  Some say it is called that because of the walkways are shaped like a pretzel and others say it is because of the pretzel vendors that were there back in the day.
Great place for kids. Highly recommend adult supervision. There is a dog park.
Small but good if in need.

Love those orange cookies from the one cookie lady, the sweet corn from the Amish people and the dog treats from the one vendor were great. Excellent place to visit and buy some fantastic produce from some great people and sometimes enjoy live bands that play great music.
Well kept family place in manayunk for kids and dogs.
Great park for kids dogs and adults alike!

Pretzel Park is a great place to go for the whole family. It has a dog park and a playground. We were there for ShakesBEER in the park which is always a fun event put on by the Manayunk Theatre Company. If you enjoy your time here don't forget to support the park through the Friends of Pretzel Park.
Nice park with a good playground for kids. Pretty small though.
One of the best parks in Philly, with a fenced in dog park, decent sized green space, and newly redone playground.
Cool doggos and hot ladies. i a vegades, los dos.
Clean and well played out for optimal usage for all goers
Nice, cool and flat...plenty of space for kids and animals...
Park es un ermoso lugar para recrearce al juntos de muchas familia con muchos albole y entretenimintos es un lugar bello especial para mi familias
Dog park, new playground, farmer's market on Saturdays, events, Park's on Tap, across the street from a beautiful and friendly Catholic Church, st John's
The updates are awesome! My kids love it here!

Nice neighborhood park. Nothing fancy, a couple swings, some monkey bars. Lots of shade trees (some good for climbing), plenty of room to run around but not big enough to get lost. Benches to sit on, a book exchange, and a dog park off to the side.
Play time
Small dog park near downtown manayunk. Very muddy overall but gated nonetheless.
Awesome
Newly renovated playground is awesome!

Beautiful park convinently located only minutes from Main Street Manayunk! Great opeb spaces that sometimes host vendors and acts as event spaces, a free mini library, jungle gym for the kids, and a dog park for your dogg-o. Everyone I met there has been pretty nice - I'd recommend stopping by!

The park is a good size and has a nice "airlock" style gate. The walls/fences are sturdy and are high enough to keep most dogs in. There is a working dog fountain so they have unlimited water, and the entire area is shaded and comfortable. All in all, a great dog park.
The park is wonderful after the playground remodel!
My pup loves it
The playground has been newly renovated Spring 2019 and it is an amazing ropes climbing coarse with slides and swing sets.
I was going to Stations @ St. John the Baptist for Stations of the Cross.

A lovely green oasis in the heart of Manayunk. It has a nice dog park and a brand new playground was just installed. There are always community events going on here, so make sure you check out the events sign by Cresson Street entrance.
Great park and fenced dog park. Unfortunately the water does not work at the dog park, bring your own.

This is a nice park to bring kids to. It's not very big but the equipment is well maintained. There is also a separate dog park area. There isn't much parking nearby or bathrooms though, but a great place if you live within walking distance.
Good location with a great view of a beautiful church architecture. I wish it is larger and greener.

I love going to the little dog park with Bella. She always finds toys and whatnot and looks forward to our walks. It's a small park but has a playground for kids and some adults. Theres also a little leave a book-take a book library that no one uses, but at least it's there. Maybe someone will leave a postcard there someday for someone else. One can only dream.
Overall, cute park.
Perfect little neighborhood park.  Dog park area.  Playground is falling into disrepair.  Room to kick a ball or have little Jimmy learn to ride his bike.
Little on the muddy side.  Very well kept.

Who let the dogs out!! This Pretzel-themed park has attractions such as a dog park, green spaces, trails, a playground for the kids, and a very impressive statue of a pretzel!! Great place to spend a Saturday
Nice

Great park. Events are held in the park in Spring, Summer and early fall. There is a dog park for large breed dogs. There is a playground for the kids. Most of the neighborhood does alot to help keep the park clean.
It's a nice park but the dog area and damage to the kids play area really lower the value of a walk-through
Nice enough. Surprised no water fountain with little lighting and no outlets for children to charge phones in case of emergencies.  Should be a standard in my opinion.
Nothing to do there you can sit and relax that's about it and the kids playground is horrible. I give it no stars at all.
It was a decent park, however some of the gear at the playground needs repair.
Great Community Park in a vibrant neighborhood

author_title: Humanity's last chance if there is one

review_text: Doggie paradise

This is a beautiful place and nice dog park but seriously needs a taller fence along the brick wall and in the corner. It's very unsafe. My dog is 30lbs and small but his prey drive kicks in when he sees the squirrels and he jumped on top of the highest point of the brick wall and walked on top then was loose in the park. Luckily he listens  to me but still I shouldn't have to worry about my dog escaping at an actual dog park.
Much fun,great music, except for the truck, bad mother shuckers, not good...
Atmosphere was pleasant
Dog park
There's a pretzel in the park what's not to love
A nice green Oasis amidst Manayunk. The park features a central green space and pretzel sculpture, a dog park, and a playground. Check out the farmer's market on Saturdays 10-2p!
Nice little park.
It is a park

Nice bit of nature in the city. There is a church on either side of the park. Down the hill is a cobblestone road under and just past that is the main road. I saw a number if benches and friendly people walking their dogs or just hanging out.
Nice little park. Has a dog park and stuff for kids. Parking is hard. But anywhere around there is hard to park.
Beautiful park in the heart of manayunk.  Nice dog run and awesome farmers market on Saturday.
It's a park w a pretzel statue
Cute spot Farmer's market every Saturday from 10 am to 2 pm.
Local park, with dog area.
Dogs of all sizes get to have fun and run around beautiful playground very clean and very nice people in a great neighborhood
Great dog park
Nice clean little park, with cool events and a neighborhood book deposit. The dog park is awesome and a great place to hangout for a bit.
Good playground and nice dog park. Also lots of shade and sun. There is also a free library book box there.
Nice clean dog park. There was one large puddle, but that isn‚Äôt anything that could not reasonably be avoided
Check out the farmers markets and events in the spring and fall!
Perfect small park. Kid and dog friendly. Great farmers market. Wish the dog park had a little more mulch because when it rains, it turns into a mud pit for several days.

It's a small park with a small playground right behind the train tracks. The playground could definitely use a make over, but it's good enough to give your kids some space to get some energy out if your in the neighborhood.
Not for kids over 2... üòï
Its a pretty park but if your kids are over the she of 2, they'll be bored.
Dog park, a playground,  young to middle aged people. View is everything you need when coming to manayunk
Parks on Tap was here. Nice relaxing afternoon in a hammock

This is a Nice little park. Very tiny space with a great vibe. The little park has a little library in park , people comes here to borrow books , while they borrow one , they leave one book as an exchange and a few features for kids as a play ground. Nice and relaxing place .
Beautiful tiny local park with dog area

Mulch foundation, so be ready for your dog to get somewhat dirty. Good that there's a water fountain. One size park, so small and big dogs will have to share the space. Be mindful of your dog near the wall, it's a short wall and can be jumped. Depending if you're up or down the hill, the sidewalk will be a short or tall drop.
Great place to take the dogs. Awesome park different events each week going one. Definitely a good place to visit if you live in the area
Located in Manayunk. Attended the fall festival which was a nice event.. live band and vendors.  Manayunk is a great section to visit if you coming to Philly. Lots of restaurants and shops.
One of the larger parks in the area, if you like Pokemon go there are 5 pokestops including a gym here
Something going on most weekends. Lively little park.
A real sense of community. There is a dog park, playground, and a farmers marker during season.
Nice playground and dog run.  Parks on Tap was fun.
Excellent dog park. Nice play zone for kids. Close to manayunk main Street restaurants and shopping.
Convenient dog park. They put the occasional work into it but it gets run down
Tiny park
Park could use a revamp but lots of local events.

Pretzel Park very nice neighborhood park. It's a great place for a family picnic, play time for children, and with plenty of mature trees to sit under while talking with old friends, making new friends, and otherwise taking a moment to appreciate the local birds, bats and squirrels.
Beautiful little park with a playground and fenced in dog run.
The park is always kept in nice condition. There's a small dog park and groups from the neighborhood have frequent events there.
Very nice place to relax and quiet
Cute little park in Manayunk. Not a ton to do but a good break before you climb the hills.
I really like this park. They have a nice dog run and a well-maintained play area.
Its name says it all
Beautiful, well kept park. Very friendly people!
Neat
Beautiful park in Manayunk with a closed fenced area for dogs to play. Only downfall is the park itself always seems to be trashed with trash and beer bottles.
Nice place to hang out
Great location and wonderful people, but the dog park is pure mud.
Farmer's markets all summer, friendly playground parents, dog park, yard for frisbee, good views, wonderful little park. Loses a star for size but is otherwise perfect.
I've been going there since I was a kid. It's always been a park for the school kids to go after school. It's pretty clean. Little dog area and new plays sets for the little ones.
Small but functional dog park, with a doggy water fountain in the warmer months and free poop bags year round!
Nice place to bring dogs!
Has a great doggie park!
No separation of small and large dogs but beautiful grounds and clean.
Clean and dog friendly thanks to Philadelphia parks and recreation.
Clean and nicely kept.
Family friendly park with a great dog park.
Nice dog park. Very nice place to take a walk.
Nice park
Well frequented city playground with a dog park. Lots of weekend activities, farmers market.

Average city park, but this one contains a fenced off dog park as well. On weekends there is a small farmers market and live entertainment when it is nice out. Great small town field in the middle of a big city.

Dog park, playground, open green space, Pretzel Park has it all. Even weekly Farmers markets. I like that it is clean and free to use. Located just off Main Street, it's a hidden gem at the heart of manayunk.

Perhaps this dog park is good for less athletic dogs, but the wall guarding the park from the street is very low. My dog easily jumped it and almost ran away. Luckily, I was able to use my come command and get her back in my arms. I cant recommend this to anyone. Too risky, the street is right next to this wall so it would be very simple for a dog to jump the wall and go straight into traffic.

A nice park in a good location. There is a fenced-off dog park portion, which is good for non-dog owners like me who don't want to deal with dogs or their messes. The park has playground equipment that seems fun, but perhaps challenging for younger children. The park is a welcome stroll as we walk from the area around the historic churches to Main Street.
Great small park,  but playground needs some attention

This is a great park for dogs, but it is just OK for kids. The playground equipment looks more like a work of sculpture art than actual playground equipment for kids. There are a few swings, a small slide, and that is about it. Most of the playground equipment is run down and has been vandalized by the local teenagers; kids will be kids. However, this is the best park in the area and I REALLY hope the neighborhood upgrades playground soon.
Nice clean park with room for your dog to run and burn off calories. To bad I have a small Pomeranian and she can fit threw the bars of the fence. not good for small dogs.
Philly has the best parks!
Neat little park, with water & bags. Wish we had one in Fairmount.
